body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

Create a project with a subdirectory, `subd`.  Place the following mcve into that subdirectory:

```verilog
module	memdev(i_clk, i_addr, o_data);
	parameter	DW=32;
	parameter	HEXFILE="rom.hex";
	input	wire			i_clk;
	input	wire	[4:0]  	i_addr;
	output	reg	[(DW-1):0]	o_data;

	reg	[(DW-1):0]	mem	[0:31];
	initial	$readmemh(HEXFILE, mem);
	always @(posedge i_clk)
		o_data <= mem[sw_addr];

endmodule
```

Also, place the `rom.hex` file into the same subdirectory.

Now imagine that this Verilog file is part of a larger project with many pieces.  You might wish to synthesize it from the basic directory rather than the subdirectory using a command such as,

`yosys -p 'read -sv subd/mcve.v; synth'`

## Expected behavior

I would expect an option to have the hex file read from either the local directory, the directory that the `.v` file is found within, or otherwise a configurable parameter indicating where the associated data files might be found.

## Actual behavior

Yosys currently checks files relative to the location where yosys was called only.  As a result, it cannot find this hex file.

